# ğŸ§® Terminal Kanban Board

A visually appealing **terminal-based Kanban board**  
powered by the [Rich](https://github.com/Textualize/rich) library.  

Tasks are organized in three statuses:   
**TODO**, **NOW**, and **DONE**,  
displayed either **horizontally or vertically**.

Each task belongs to a **custom category**,  
and each category is assigned a **unique color** for visual grouping.

Data is stored in a simple **CSV file**,  
and all configuration is handled with a **Python dictionary file**.

---

## ğŸ›  Features

- ğŸ“¦ Three colored status columns: `TODO`, `NOW`, `DONE`
- ğŸ—‚ Tasks have `id`, `title`, `description`, `category`, `status`
- ğŸ¨ Custom categories with persistent color assignment
- âŒ¨ï¸ Vim-inspired commands like `:a`, `:m`, `:w`, `:q`
- ğŸ§  Intelligent ID reuse
- ğŸ” Layout switching: vertical (default) or horizontal
- ğŸ” Filtering, sorting, and searching tasks
- ğŸ§¹ Clean visual interface with bordered Rich panels

